  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Sexual and Reproductive Health Clinic - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_sexual_and_reproductive_health_clinic">Sexual and Reproductive Health Clinic</xref>
 is an 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_out-patient_clinic">Out-Patient Clinic</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_sexual_and_reproductive_health_clinic">Sexual and Reproductive Health Clinic</xref>
 is a clinic specifically to provide 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_sexual_and_reproductive_health_service">Sexual and Reproductive Health Services</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
This includes non-NHS 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATION</xref>
 clinics from which these services are commissioned by the NHS.        </p>
      <p>
Clinics run by 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_consultant">CONSULTANTS</xref>
 are included under 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_consultant_clinic">Consultant Clinic</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
It should be noted that work in 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_general_medical_practitioner">GENERAL MEDICAL PRACTITIONER</xref>
 surgeries or 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_general_medical_practitioner">GENERAL MEDICAL PRACTITIONER</xref>
 work on hospital premises is excluded.        </p>
  </div>
